{
  "answer": "This catalogue of karmic disfigurements appears in two works in the corpus.\n\n**In *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 12:**\n\n> A gold thief obtains diseased nails; a liquor-drinker, black teeth; a slayer of a Brahmana, consumptive disease; and a defiler of a guru's bed, skin disease.[^1]  \n> A slanderer obtains a stinking nose; an informer, a stinking mouth; a grain-thief, a deficient limb; and an adulterator, a superfluous one.[^2]  \n> A food-thief obtains indigestion; a speech-thief, muteness; a clothes-thief, vitiligo; and a horse-thief, lameness.[^3]\n\n**In *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, Chapter 45:**\n\n> A liquor-drinker becomes one with black teeth.[^4]  \n> A gold-thief becomes one with bad nails.[^5]  \n> A slanderer becomes one with a foul-smelling nose.[^6]  \n> A stealer of clothes becomes one with vitiligo.[^7]  \n> A stealer of a horse becomes lame.[^8]\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 12, p-3e6ead](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-3e6ead).\n[^2]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 12, p-0dfd49](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-0dfd49).\n[^3]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 12, p-a549f5](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-a549f5).\n[^4]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 45, p-775026](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/45/translation/#p-775026).\n[^5]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 45, p-7d5c3a](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/45/translation/#p-7d5c3a).\n[^6]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 45, p-343f82](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/45/translation/#p-343f82).\n[^7]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 45, p-fc8a10](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/45/translation/#p-fc8a10).\n[^8]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 45, p-a5cf34](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/45/translation/#p-a5cf34).",
